<Project Sdk="Dalamud.NET.Sdk/15.0.0">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <Author>LastOnionKnight</Author>
    <Name>Tonberry Tactics</Name>
    <InternalName>GearGoblin</InternalName>
    <AssemblyVersion>0.6.6.0</AssemblyVersion>
    <FileVersion>0.6.6.0</FileVersion>
    <Version>0.6.6.0</Version>
    <!-- v0.6.6.0 opens a new architectural era for the plugin. The
         StatusPanelInjector-based character-panel injection that
         dominated the v0.4.x–v0.6.5.x lineage is now feature-complete
         on its native-panel surface; BUG-001 (header ghost text) and
         BUG-002 (right-aligned cell overflow into the label region)
         both closed in the v0.6.5.5 H6-B + label-cell-rerouting
         intervention. Going forward we add a dedicated Character tab
         to the /tt window. That tab will absorb the materia advisor,
         substat sheet, audit display, and equipped gear into one
         designed surface that we fully own — eliminating the entire
         cloned-cell-overflow class of bugs at the root. v0.6.6 ships
         the skeleton of that tab; visual polish lands in v0.6.6.1+.
         The StatusPanelInjector remains shipped through the v0.6.x
         line for backward compatibility and side-by-side validation;
         it gets a deprecation note in v0.6.7 and is removed in v0.7.0.

         Pure numeric versioning (Option 3) preserved from the v0.6.5.x
         decision. UI/MainWindow.cs ResolveVersion() retains the
         InformationalVersion-preferring code path as dormant
         infrastructure but it is not actively populated. -->
    <MinimumDalamudVersion>15.0.0</MinimumDalamudVersion>
    <Punchline>BiS planner, Materia Advisor, and round-trip optimizer for FFXIV. The in-game half of Tonberry Tactics; coexists with CharacterPanelRefined.</Punchline>
    <Description>In-game half of Tonberry Tactics. v0.6.6.0 closes the BUG-001 (Materia Advisor header ghost text) and BUG-002 (advisor row left-overflow) sagas — both confirmed dead in v0.6.5.5 H6-B in-game testing — and introduces the Character tab in /tt as the strategic replacement for the native-panel injection approach. The new tab consolidates name + class + iLvl identity, substat sheet, materia advisor recommendations, and equipped gear table into one ImGui surface we fully own. Skeleton wired to live data; visual polish (Adventurer Plate aesthetic, stat-card chrome, ranked advisor rows with gain badges, striped gear table) lands incrementally in v0.6.6.x. The legacy StatusPanelInjector continues shipping in parallel for backward compat — deprecation notice in v0.6.7, removal in v0.7.0. Core and Web at v0.6.6.0 lockstep (version-only). See CHANGELOG.md for the full BUG-001/002 hypothesis archaeology and the Character tab roadmap.</Description>
    <RepoUrl>https://github.com/LastOnionKnight/GearGoblin</RepoUrl>
    <Tags>gear;bis;materia;etro;xivgear;raid;advisor;cpr;character-panel;tonberry-tactics</Tags>

    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>
    <LangVersion>latest</LangVersion>
    <AllowUnsafeBlocks>true</AllowUnsafeBlocks>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <!-- v0.4.7.1: brand artwork shipped alongside the DLL. Dalamud's SDK
       picks these up automatically via the Content glob and includes them
       in the plugin's install directory; runtime resolves via
       PluginInterface.AssemblyLocation.Directory + "Assets/" (see
       Services/BrandResources.cs). -->
  <ItemGroup>
    <Content Include="Assets\**\*.png">
      <CopyToOutputDirectory>PreserveNewest</CopyToOutputDirectory>
      <Pack>true</Pack>
    </Content>
  </ItemGroup>

  <!-- v0.6.0: custom .ttf fonts for IFontAtlas Phase 2. Same copy
       discipline as the brand artwork — runtime resolves the directory
       via PluginInterface.AssemblyLocation.Directory + "Assets/Fonts/"
       (see Theme/FontAtlasManager.cs). -->
  <ItemGroup>
    <Content Include="Assets\Fonts\*.ttf">
      <CopyToOutputDirectory>PreserveNewest</CopyToOutputDirectory>
      <Pack>true</Pack>
    </Content>
  </ItemGroup>

  <!--
    v0.6.3: ProjectReference to the shared GearGoblin.Core library.
    Path assumes the standard sibling-of-grandparent layout:

        D:\GearGoblin-Core-v0.1\GearGoblin.Core\        (Core, this reference's target)
        D:\GearGoblin-v0.1\GearGoblin\                  (this project)
        D:\TonberryTactics-workspace\TonberryTactics\   (web, mirrors this same reference)

    If Core lives somewhere else on your machine, update the path to
    point at your local clone. The web's csproj uses the same relative
    pattern so both halves resolve to the same library on disk.

    Plugin's existing MeldOptimizer (already job-aware via JobProfile)
    continues to function unchanged in v0.6.6 — Core integration on
    the plugin side is incremental, tracked for v0.7.x alongside the
    StatusPanelInjector removal work.
  -->
  <ItemGroup>
    <ProjectReference Include="..\..\GearGoblin-Core-v0.1\GearGoblin.Core\GearGoblin.Core.csproj" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
